**Railroads**

Historically, Pensacola was a stop on [Amtrak](/Amtrak)'s [Sunset Limited](/Sunset_Limited) route, connecting [Los Angeles](/Los_Angeles) and [Orlando, Florida](/Orlando,_Florida), from 1993 to 2005. Service east of New Orleans was suspended following damage from [Hurricane Katrina](/Hurricane_Katrina), and passenger train service has not resumed in Escambia County since.

Prior to Amtrak's establishment in 1971, Pensacola was served by the [Gulf Wind](/Gulf_Wind) service, jointly operated by the [Louisville and Nashville Railroad](/Louisville_and_Nashville_Railroad) and the [Seaboard Air Line Railroad](/Seaboard_Air_Line_Railroad) (forerunners of CSX).

Currently, freight railroad service in Escambia County includes:

*   [CSX](/CSX) operates a line from [Flomaton, Alabama](/Flomaton,_Alabama), to Pensacola.
*   The [Florida Gulf & Atlantic Railroad](/Florida_Gulf_%26_Atlantic_Railroad) acquired a significant portion of the CSX main line from Pensacola to [Jacksonville](/Jacksonville) on June 1, 2019.
*   The [Alabama & Gulf Coast Railway](/Alabama_%26_Gulf_Coast_Railway) runs a line from [Amory, Mississippi](/Amory,_Mississippi), to Pensacola, a route previously operated by the [Frisco Railway](/Frisco_Railway).

